eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is most likely to see a fifth wave of COVID-19 infections as it heads towards winter. This is according to Health Minister Joe Phaahla, who has given an update on COVID-19 in the country. WATCH: Omicron sub-variant nothing to be alarmed by: expert Phaahla has also highlighted the increase in infections that's been seen in those below the age of 20. eNCA's senior reporter Aviwe Mtila filed this report.